Description: Egypt, view of shop in Cairo. What appear to be pots, pans and utensils hanging outside arched entrances. Adult male standing in front of shop, child sitting beside, wearing robes, head-gear. Street-sign [?] on wall. Medium: Gelatin silver print.
Producer name: Photographed by: John Frederick Clifford Hunt
Curator's comments: Circumstances: The Imperial War Museum holds photographs from the same collection with a more military content - see [HUN-] PIC DOC 66.
